  [
    "h1",
    {},
    "Possessive Pronouns"
  ],
  [
    "p",
    {},
    [
      "In Greek, possession is usually expressed using a \"weak\" form of the personal pronoun that follows the noun. To express \"own\" or for stronger emphasis, we use the word ",
      [
        "strong",
        {},
        "δικός"
      ],
      "."
    ]
  ],
  [
    "h2",
    {},
    "1. The Weak Forms (My, Your, His...)"
  ],
  [
    "p",
    {},
    "These short words always follow the noun and never change their form based on the noun's case—they only match the person and number of the owner."
  ],
  [
    "div",
    {
      "className": "content-grid mt-8"
    },
    [
      "h3",
      {},
      "Singular Owner"
    ],
